Please try to write SQL queries for the dvdrental database (check HW0 Part 3).

Order customers from customer table based on first_name ascending order and last_name descending order.
Find rental id that rental date is either 2005-05-24 or 2005-05-26
Find total number of payment transactions of each staff using on payment table.
List the full names of all customers whose address does not include the keyword “Santiago”
List the store_id of the stores with more than 200 customers.
Find all rentals that did not have the customer id as 1 or 2.


1. Order customers from customer table based on first_name ascending order and last_name descending order.

SELECT first_name, last_name
FROM customer
ORDER BY first_name ASC, last_name DESC;

2. Find rental id that rental date is either 2005-05-24 or 2005-05-26

SELECT rental_id
FROM rental
WHERE rental_date IN ('2005-05-24', '2005-05-26');

3. Find total number of payment transactions of each staff using on payment table.

SELECT staff_id, COUNT(*) AS total_payments
FROM payment
GROUP BY staff_id;

4.List the full names of all customers whose address does not include the keyword “Santiago”

SELECT first_name, last_name
FROM customer
WHERE address NOT LIKE '%Santiago%';

5. List the store_id of the stores with more than 200 customers.

SELECT store_id, COUNT(*) AS total_customers
FROM customer
GROUP BY store_id
HAVING COUNT(*) > 200;

6. Find all rentals that did not have the customer id as 1 or 2.

SELECT *
FROM rental
WHERE customer_id NOT IN (1, 2);
